# Branitz2 Project: Comprehensive A-to-Z Walkthrough

> **Multi-Agent AI System for Climate-Neutral Urban Heat Planning**
> Author: Ishantha Hewaratne · Fraunhofer IEG · Python 3.10 · MIT License

---

## 1. What the Project Does

Branitz Heat Decision is a **service-oriented, multi-agent system** that evaluates whether a residential street cluster in the Branitz settlement (Cottbus, Germany) should be heated by **District Heating (DH)** or individual **Heat Pumps (HP)**. It runs physics-based simulations, economic analysis, and deterministic decision logic — then presents results through a Streamlit UI with natural-language chat.

```mermaid
graph LR
    User((User)) -->|Chat / Click| UI[Streamlit UI]
    UI --> O[Orchestrator]
    O -->|Intent| NLU[Intent Classifier]
    O -->|Execute| EX[DynamicExecutor]
    EX --> CHA[CHA Agent]
    EX --> DHA[DHA Agent]
    EX --> ECON[Economics Agent]
    EX --> DEC[Decision Agent]
    EX --> UHDC[UHDC Report Agent]
    CHA --> S1[01_run_cha.py]
    DHA --> S2[02_run_dha.py]
    ECON --> S3[03_run_economics.py]
    DEC --> S4[cli/decision.py]
    UHDC --> S5[cli/uhdc.py]
    S1 & S2 & S3 & S4 & S5 -->|Artifacts| R[(results/)]
    R --> UI
```

