## 3. The Pipeline: Five Phases

The system runs a **sequential 5-phase pipeline**. Each phase is a standalone CLI script and a corresponding agent.

### Phase 0 — Data Preparation
- **Script**: [00_prepare_data.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/scripts/00_prepare_data.py)
- **What it does**: Loads raw GeoJSON (buildings + streets), creates street-based clusters, generates BDEW hourly heat-demand profiles (8760 × n_buildings), computes design-hour and top-N hours, and writes a UI-friendly cluster index.
- **Key modules**: [loader.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/data/loader.py), [cluster.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/data/cluster.py), [profiles.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/data/profiles.py), [typology.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/data/typology.py)
- **Outputs**: `data/processed/buildings.parquet`, `street_clusters.parquet`, `cluster_index.parquet`, `hourly_profiles.parquet`, `cluster_design_topn.json`

### Phase 1 — CHA (Cluster Heat Assessment)
- **Script**: [01_run_cha.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/scripts/01_run_cha.py) (858 lines)
- **What it does**: Builds a district heating **trunk-spur network** using street geometries, runs **pandapipes** hydraulic simulation (pressure/velocity/temperature), optimizes for convergence, validates against **EN 13941-1** compliance.
- **Key modules**:
  - [network_builder_trunk_spur.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/network_builder_trunk_spur.py) (1875 lines) — the heart of CHA; builds supply+return pipe network from street graph → building spurs
  - [convergence_optimizer.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/convergence_optimizer.py) — iterative diameter/flow adjustment
  - [heat_loss.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/heat_loss.py) — per-pipe thermal loss (U-value based)
  - [sizing_catalog.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/sizing_catalog.py) — DN-based pipe catalog with technical specs
  - [kpi_extractor.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/kpi_extractor.py) — extracts KPIs from pandapipes results
  - Validators: [design_validator.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/design_validator.py), [hydraulic_checks.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/hydraulic_checks.py), [thermal_checks.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/thermal_checks.py), [geospatial_checks.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cha/geospatial_checks.py)
- **Outputs**: `results/cha/{cluster_id}/cha_kpis.json`, `network.pickle`, `interactive_map.html` (velocity, temperature, pressure maps)

### Phase 2 — DHA (Decentralized Heat Assessment)
- **Script**: [02_run_dha.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/scripts/02_run_dha.py) (458 lines)
- **What it does**: Models per-building heat pumps on the **low-voltage (LV) electrical grid**, runs **pandapower** load flow, checks for voltage violations and line overloading, evaluates smart grid mitigation strategies and grid reinforcement.
- **Key modules**:
  - [grid_builder.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/grid_builder.py) — builds LV grid topology
  - [loadflow.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/loadflow.py) — pandapower load flow analysis
  - [hosting_capacity.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/hosting_capacity.py) — how many HPs the grid can handle
  - [mitigations.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/mitigations.py) & [smart_grid_strategies.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/smart_grid_strategies.py) — voltage regulation strategies
  - [reinforcement_optimizer.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/reinforcement_optimizer.py) — cable/transformer upgrade planning
  - [bdew_base_loads.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/dha/bdew_base_loads.py) — BDEW standard load profiles
- **Outputs**: `results/dha/{cluster_id}/dha_kpis.json`, `hp_lv_map.html`

### Phase 3 — Economics
- **Script**: [03_run_economics.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/scripts/03_run_economics.py) (438 lines)
- **Dependencies**: Requires Phase 1 (CHA) + Phase 2 (DHA) results
- **What it does**: Computes **Levelized Cost of Heat (LCOH)** using the CRF method for both DH and HP, calculates CO₂ emissions, runs **Monte Carlo** uncertainty propagation (500 samples default), performs sensitivity analysis and stress testing.
- **Key modules**:
  - [lcoh.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/lcoh.py) — LCOH calculation with marginal cost allocation (PlantContext)
  - [monte_carlo.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/monte_carlo.py) — statistical robustness via sampling
  - [co2.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/co2.py) — carbon emission factors (DH vs HP)
  - [sensitivity.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/sensitivity.py) & [stress_tests.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/stress_tests.py) — parameter sensitivity
  - [params.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/params.py) — economic parameters (discount rates, lifecycle costs)
  - [plant_context.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/economics/plant_context.py) — Cottbus CHP plant shared asset context
- **Outputs**: `results/economics/{cluster_id}/economics_deterministic.json`, `economics_monte_carlo.json`, `sensitivity_analysis.json`, `stress_tests.json`

### Phase 4 — Decision
- **CLI**: [cli/decision.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cli/decision.py)
- **Dependencies**: CHA + DHA + Economics results
- **What it does**: Builds a canonical **KPI Contract** from all upstream outputs, applies **deterministic rules** to recommend DH or HP — purely rule-based, never LLM-driven.
- **Key modules**:
  - [kpi_contract.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/kpi_contract.py) — assembles CHA + DHA + Economics KPIs into a single auditable contract
  - [rules.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py) — **`decide_from_contract()`**: feasibility gate → cost comparison → MC robustness → CO₂ tiebreaker
  - [schemas.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/schemas.py) — TypedDict schemas + ContractValidator + REASON_CODES
- **Decision Logic**: (1) If only one is feasible → pick it; (2) If costs differ >5% → pick cheaper; (3) If costs close → use Monte Carlo robustness (≥70% wins = robust); (4) CO₂ tiebreaker
- **Outputs**: `results/decision/{cluster_id}/decision_{cluster_id}.json`

### Phase 5 — UHDC (Urban Heat Decision Communication)
- **CLI**: [cli/uhdc.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/cli/uhdc.py)
- **Dependencies**: Decision results
- **What it does**: Generates a stakeholder-facing HTML report with glassmorphism design, decision banner, executive summary, embedded charts, metric cards with confidence intervals, and map iframes.
- **Key modules**:
  - [report_builder.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/uhdc/report_builder.py) (988 lines) — Jinja2-based HTML report with Bootstrap 5 styling
  - [explainer.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/uhdc/explainer.py) — LLM-generated explanations (Gemini) with template fallback
  - [safety_validator.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/uhdc/safety_validator.py) — validates LLM explanations don't contradict the deterministic decision
- **Outputs**: `results/uhdc/{cluster_id}/uhdc_report_{cluster_id}.html`

