## 4. Agent Architecture (3 Layers)

The system has a deliberate **3-layer agent hierarchy**, analogized as a **restaurant kitchen**:

### Layer 1 — ADK Agents (`adk/`)
- [agent.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/adk/agent.py): `BaseADKAgent` → `DataPrepAgent`, `CHAAgent`, `DHAAgent`, `EconomicsAgent`, `DecisionAgent`, `UHDCAgent`
- [tools.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/adk/tools.py): 6 tool functions (`prepare_data_tool`, `run_cha_tool`, `run_dha_tool`, `run_economics_tool`, `run_decision_tool`, `run_uhdc_tool`) — each constructs a CLI command and runs it via `subprocess`
- [policies.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/adk/policies.py): 4 guardrails:
  1. **`llm_cannot_decide`** — LLM cannot modify or override decisions
  2. **`readonly_artifacts`** — upstream artifacts are immutable
  3. **`required_phases`** — enforces dependency order
  4. **`deterministic_outputs`** — blocks random decision paths

### Layer 2 — Domain Agents (`agents/domain_agents.py`)
"Station chefs" with caching. Each delegates to its ADK counterpart:
- `DataPrepAgent`, `CHAAgent`, `DHAAgent`, `EconomicsAgent`, `DecisionAgent`, `ValidationAgent`, `UHDCAgent`, `WhatIfAgent`
- Each implements `can_handle(intent)`, `execute(street_id, context)`, and cache checking

### Layer 3 — Orchestrator + Executor (`agents/`)
| File | Role |
|:---|:---|
| [orchestrator.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/agents/orchestrator.py) | `BranitzOrchestrator` — **routes** natural-language requests by classifying intent, then dispatching to `DynamicExecutor` or answering directly |
| [executor.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/agents/executor.py) | `DynamicExecutor` — **"Head Chef"** that creates dependency-ordered agent plans, runs them sequentially, integrates results |
| [conversation.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/agents/conversation.py) | `ConversationManager` — multi-turn context (handles "What about LCOH?" follow-ups, metric switching, modification chaining) |
| [fallback.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/agents/fallback.py) | `CapabilityGuardrail` — explicit boundaries for what the system *cannot* do, with graceful LLM-powered explanations |

---

## 5. NLU (Natural Language Understanding)

[intent_classifier.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/nlu/intent_classifier.py) uses **Gemini** (google.genai SDK) to classify user queries into intents:

| Intent | Triggers |
|:---|:---|
| `CO2_COMPARISON` | "Compare CO2 emissions" |
| `LCOH_COMPARISON` | "Compare costs" |
| `VIOLATION_ANALYSIS` | "Check pressure violations" |
| `NETWORK_DESIGN` | "Show network layout" |
| `WHAT_IF_SCENARIO` | "What if we remove 2 houses?" |
| `EXPLAIN_DECISION` | "Why was DH recommended?" |
| `CAPABILITY_QUERY` | "What can you do?" |

Falls back to **keyword matching** when LLM is unavailable.

---

## 6. Validation & Safety

### Logic Auditor (`validation/`)
[logic_auditor.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/validation/logic_auditor.py) (911 lines)
- **TNLI Model**: Textual Natural Language Inference — checks if LLM explanations are entailed, neutral, or contradictory vs. KPI data
- **ClaimExtractor**: Regex-based quantitative claim extraction + cross-validation against canonical KPIs
- **Feedback Loop**: If contradictions detected, triggers LLM regeneration with enriched context
- Reports: `verified_rate`, `unverified_rate`, `contradiction_rate`

### Safety Validator (`uhdc/safety_validator.py`)
Validates that LLM-generated explanations don't contradict the deterministic decision.

---

## 7. UI Layer

[app.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/ui/app.py) (1685 lines) — Streamlit application with:
- **Sidebar**: Street selector, scenario catalog buttons, chat input with example prompts
- **Main tabs**: 3D Map, Feasibility (CHA sub-tab + DHA sub-tab), Economics, Decision, Report, AI Chat
- **Services** ([services.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/ui/services.py)):
  - `ClusterService` — loads cluster index, buildings, geometries, profiles
  - `JobService` — starts background subprocess jobs with dependency resolution
  - `ResultService` — polls `results/` directory for artifacts
- **Registry** ([registry.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/ui/registry.py)): `SCENARIO_REGISTRY` maps scenario keys → CLI command templates + expected outputs + dependencies
- **LLM Router** ([llm.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/ui/llm.py)): Gemini API integration for chat

