## 8. Data Flow: End-to-End Example

A user asks: **"Is District Heating feasible for Heinrich Zille Straße?"**

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant UI as Streamlit UI
    participant O as Orchestrator
    participant NLU as IntentClassifier
    participant EX as DynamicExecutor
    participant CHA as CHAAgent
    participant S as 01_run_cha.py
    participant R as results/cha/

    U->>UI: "Is DH feasible here?"
    UI->>O: route_request(query, cluster_id)
    O->>NLU: classify_intent(query)
    NLU-->>O: {intent: NETWORK_DESIGN}
    O->>EX: execute("NETWORK_DESIGN", "ST010_...")
    EX->>CHA: execute("ST010_...")
    CHA->>CHA: _check_cha_cache() → miss
    CHA->>S: subprocess.run(01_run_cha.py ...)
    S->>S: load_cluster_data()
    S->>S: build_trunk_spur_network()
    S->>S: pandapipes.pipeflow()
    S->>R: write cha_kpis.json + maps
    CHA-->>EX: AgentResult(success=True, data=kpis)
    EX-->>O: integrated response
    O-->>UI: {answer: "...", viz: map, data: kpis}
    UI-->>U: Display map + metrics
```

---

## 9. Key Design Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|:---|:---|
| **LLM Cannot Decide** | Decision logic is 100% deterministic rules ([rules.py](file:///Users/ishanthahewaratne/Documents/Reserch%20New/Branitz2/src/branitz_heat_decision/decision/rules.py)); LLM only generates explanations |
| **Artifact Communication** | Components decouple via JSON/HTML files in `results/`; no in-memory coupling |
| **Dual Triggers** | Same pipeline runs from UI (subprocess) or programmatically (ADK agents) |
| **Graceful Degradation** | `CapabilityGuardrail` explicitly lists what the system *cannot* do and offers alternatives |
| **Reproducibility** | Monte Carlo uses fixed seeds; deterministic outputs policy enforced |
| **Validation Safety** | TNLI-based logic auditing catches LLM hallucinations before they reach users |

